\sum_{k=1}^\infty{\frac{1}{k^2}} = \frac{\pi^2}{6}\ 
\sum_{k=1}^\infty{\frac{(-1)^{k+1}}{k^2}} = \frac{\pi^2}{12}\ 
\frac{1}{1^2} - \frac{1}{2^2} + \frac{1}{3^2} - \frac{1}{4^2} + \frac{1}{5^2} - \frac{1}{6^2} + \dots\\ =\left(\frac{1}{1^2} + \frac{1}{2^2} + \frac{1}{3^2} + \dots\right) - 2\left(\frac{1}{2^2} + \frac{1}{4^2} + \frac{1}{6^2} + \dots\right)\\ = \frac{\pi^2}{6} - \frac{2}{2^2}\left(\frac{1}{1^2} + \frac{1}{2^2} + \frac{1}{3^2} + \dots\right)\\ = \frac{\pi^2}{6} - \frac{1}{2}\cdot\frac{\pi^2}{6}\\ = \frac{\pi^2}{12}
\sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{(-1)^{k+1}}{k^2}=\sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^2}-2\sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{1}{(2k)^2}=\frac12\sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{1}{k^2}=\frac{\pi^2}{12}
A=\sum_{k=1}^\infty{\frac{1}{(2k-1)^2}}
B=\sum_{k=1}^\infty{\frac{1}{(2k)^2}}
A+B=\frac\pi6
B=\frac14\cdot\frac\pi6=\frac\pi{24}
A-B=(A+B)-2B=\dotsb
